        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                What is the square of: <m>1.21</m>?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>1.21^2</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                There are several approaches that one can use to find the square of <m>1.21</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>In this approach, we convert <m>1.21</m> to a fraction.</p>
                            <p><m>1.21 = \frac{121}{100}</m></p>
                            <p>Then, we square the fraction <m>\frac{121}{100}</m>, multiply the numerator by itself and the denominator by itself.</p>
                            <p><m>\frac{121}{100} \times \frac{121}{100} = \frac{121 \times 121}{100 \times 100} = \frac{14641}{10000}</m></p>
                            <p>We finally convert the fraction <m>\frac{14641}{10000}</m> to a decimal by dividing the numerator by the denominator.</p>
                            <p><m>\frac{14641}{10000} = 1.4641</m></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    What is the value of <m>2.35^2</m>?
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>2.35^2</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>To find <m>2.35^2</m> we need to calculate <m>2.35 \times 2.35</m></p>
                            <p>Convert <m>2.35</m> to a whole number by multiplying it by 100.</p>
                            <p><m>2.35 \times 100 = 235</m></p>
                            <p>Then, we have: <m>235 \times 235 </m></p>
                            <tabular>
                                <row>
                                    <cell halign="right"><m>235</m></cell>
                                    <cell></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell halign="right" bottom="medium"><m>\times 235</m></cell>
                                    <cell></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell halign="right"><m>1175</m></cell>
                                    <cell halign="left"><m>{\color{blue}235} \times {\color{blue}5}</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell halign="right"><m>705</m></cell>
                                    <cell halign="left"><m>{\color{blue}235} \times {\color{blue}3}</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell halign="right" bottom="medium"><m>+ 470</m></cell>
                                    <cell halign="left"><m> {\color{blue}235} \times {\color{blue}2}</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell halign="right" bottom="medium"><m>55\,225</m></cell>
                                </row>
                            </tabular>
                            <p>Since we initially removed two decimal places from each number <m>2.35</m> (multiplying by 100 for both), we must divide the final result by <m>100^2  = 10000</m> to restore the decimal:</p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> 55225 \div 10000 = \frac{55225}{10000} \amp = 5.5225  </mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = 5.5225 </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
